    feat: Finalize game loop mechanics and visual polish (Phase 1 Ratification)
    
    This commit ratifies the SDL2 simulator phase by finalizing the core game loop,
    combat mechanics, and visual feedback systems. The engine is now feature-complete
    for the transition to bare-metal STM32 hardware.
    
    Key Updates:
    - Weapon Logic: Implemented a semi-automatic firing state machine using a
      cooldown timer. Added 3-frame visual recoil animation (IDs 421-423) and
      differentiated 'out-of-ammo' states using negative timer values to prevent
      visual glitches.
    - Hit-Scan Combat: Developed a self-contained local-camera-matrix targeting
      system that correctly identifies the closest enemy in the player's crosshairs.
    - Visual Polish (Juice): Added a modularized checkerboard damage flash and a
      stochastic "pixel-dissolve" death screen that noise-fills the frame buffer
      without requiring additional SRAM for double buffering.
    - Entity Balancing: Tuned Guard AI attack ranges and fixed item pickup bugs;
      implemented health clamping at 100% to maintain game balance.
    - Math Robustness: Switched delta_dist calculations to float-assisted logic
      to prevent 16.16 fixed-point overflows at extreme ray angles, eliminating
      1px vertical rendering artifacts.
    
    The engine now supports a full Play -> Death -> Restart cycle. Phase 1 is
    officially closed.

